snippet for placeholder images: 


 "Placeholder Image": {
"scope": "html, javascript,typescript",
"prefix": "placeh",
"body": [
"<img src=\"https://via.placeholder.com/${1|50,100,200|}x${2|50,100,200|}\" alt=\"placeholder img\" class=\"img-fluid\" />", "$0"
],
"description": "Insert a placeholder image"
}

Announcement: "git commands for first commit: git init…"

Herbert Brown
Created Aug 25Aug 25 – Deleted
This post is visible to all teachers in this class. It will be permanently deleted in 10 days.
git commands for first commit:

  • git init
  • git add --all
  • git commit -m "first commit"
  • git branch -M main
  • git remote (url)
  • git push


git commands for following commits

  • git add --all
  • git commit -m "message"
  • git push

Post by Aaron Paden

Aaron Paden
Created Aug 24Aug 24 – Deleted
This post is visible to all teachers in this class. It will be permanently deleted in 9 days.
I can't remember if this came up when we were going over it before, but I found this on stackoverflow. It generates CSS to change the color of an image. For example, it's useful in the bloom project if you want the social nav icons to change color on hover.


The icon needs to be black for it to work, and the side text explains that to make this happen, you need to put "brightness(0) saturate(100%)" at the beginning of the filter. You may also need to click "compute filter" a few times to get good results.


https://codepen.io/sosuke/pen/Pjoqqp

Announcement: "Git Commands, and branch example git…"

Ethan Daniels
Created Aug 10Aug 10 – Deleted
This post is visible to all teachers in this class. It will be permanently deleted today.
Git Commands, and branch example

  • git init -> initializes the git repo locally
  • git remote add origin LINK -> Links your file with your repository on github.
  • git add --all -> Adds all of the files and new files to the git repo
  • git commit -m "Message" -> Commits the changes and adds a message. Do not forget to make the message relevant to the changes made
  • git branch -M main -> creates a new branch main
  • git push -u origin main -> pushes your changes to github repo that you created
  • git pull -> pulls from your repo to your computer
I also have attached a git flow chart. This is just a reference for later use.

I don't know if Herb mentioned it while I was working, but it looks like there are ways to do reflections with CSS, but they aren't currently standard across all browsers according to MDN. Announcement: "const express = require('express');…"

Bryce Mullican
Created Mar 2Mar 2 – Deleted
This post is visible to all teachers in this class. It will be permanently deleted today.
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const port = 3000;

app.get('/', (req, res) => { // http://localhost:${port}/
// res.send('Hola Mundo!');
res.sendFile(__dirname + '/index.html');
});

app.get('/about', (req, res) => { // http://localhost:${port}/about
// res.send('This is my about page yo!');
res.sendFile(__dirname + '/about.html');
});

app.get('/portfolio', (req, res) => {
// res.send('This is my portfolio page yo!');
res.sendFile(__dirname + '/portfolio.html');
});

// http://localhost:3000/sum?num1=2&num2=3
app.get('/sum', (req, res) => {
const query = req.query;
res.send( `${Number(query.num1) + Number(query.num2)}` );
});

app.get('*', (req, res) => {
res.send('<h1>404</h1>');
});

app.listen(port, () => {
console.log(`Server is running at http://localhost:${port}`);
});

Announcement: "DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS `dentist`;…"

Bryce Mullican
Created Feb 23Feb 23 (Edited Feb 24) – Deleted
This post is visible to all teachers in this class. It will be permanently deleted today.
DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS `dentist`;
CREATE DATABASE `dentist`;
USE `dentist`;

CREATE TABLE `status` (
`id` tinyint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
`status` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
);

INSERT INTO `status` (`status`)
VALUES ('active'),('complete'),('canceled');

CREATE TABLE `service` (
`id` mediumint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, -- `id` != `ID`
`service_name` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
`bill` decimal(8,2) DEFAULT 0, -- 100,000.00 -> 999,999.99 != `BILL`
PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
);

INSERT INTO `service` (`service_name`, `bill`)
VALUES ('cleaning', 25.00),('crown', 140.00),('filling', 200.00);

CREATE TABLE `gender` (
`id` tinyint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, -- 255
`gender_name` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
);

INSERT INTO `gender` (`gender_name`)
VALUES ('female'), ('male'), ('non binary'), ('did not disclose');

CREATE TABLE `city` (
`id` smallint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
`city_name` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
);

INSERT INTO `city` (`city_name`)
VALUES ('Jackson'), ('Ridgeland'), ('Madison');

CREATE TABLE `insurance` (
`id` tinyint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
`insurance_co` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
);

INSERT INTO `insurance` (`insurance_co`)
VALUES ('Allstar'), ('Care-A-Lot'), ('Swindle Insurance');

CREATE TABLE `allergy` (
`id` mediumint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
`allergen` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
);

INSERT INTO `allergy` (`allergen`)
VALUES ('Lavender'), ('Peanut'), ('Seafood');

CREATE TABLE `medication` (
`id` mediumint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
`medicine` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
);

INSERT INTO `medication` (`medicine`)
VALUES ('humira'), ('opioids'), ('prednisone');

CREATE TABLE `patient` (
`id` smallint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
`lname` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
`fname` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
`ssn` varchar(64) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
`dob` date NOT NULL,
`email` varchar(255),
`phone` varchar(10) NOT NULL,
`street` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
`apt_number` varchar(5),
`zip` varchar(15) NOT NULL,
`guard_last` varchar(30) DEFAULT NULL,
`guard_first` varchar(30) DEFAULT NULL,
`balance` decimal(8,2),
`gender_id` tinyint UNSIGNED NOT NULL, -- 255 === 255
-- `gender_id` tinyint NOT NULL -- 127 != 255
`city_id` smallint UNSIGNED NOT NULL,
`primary_ins_id` tinyint UNSIGNED NOT NULL,
`secondary_ins_id` tinyint UNSIGNED DEFAULT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
CONSTRAINT fk_gender_id FOREIGN KEY (gender_id) REFERENCES gender(`id`),
CONSTRAINT fk_city_id FOREIGN KEY (city_id) REFERENCES city(`id`),
CONSTRAINT fk_primary_ins_id FOREIGN KEY (primary_ins_id) REFERENCES insurance(`id`),
CONSTRAINT fk_secondary_ins_id FOREIGN KEY (secondary_ins_id) REFERENCES insurance(`id`)
);

CREATE TABLE `cc` (

`card_number` varchar(30) NOT NULL,
`exp_date` date NOT NULL,
`cvv` smallint NOT NULL,
`card_zip` varchar(15) NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
CONSTRAINT fk_cc_patient_id FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(`id`)

CREATE TABLE `appointment` (
`id` mediumint UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
`patient_id` smallint UNSIGNED NOT NULL,
`date` date NOT NULL, -- 'YYYY-MM-DD'
`time` time NOT NULL, -- 'hh:mm:ss'
`status_id` tinyint UNSIGNED,
`notes` text,
PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
CONSTRAINT fk_apt_patient_id FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(`id`),
CONSTRAINT fk_apt_status_id FOREIGN KEY (status_id) REFERENCES status(`id`)
);

SELECT
p.lname,
p.fname,
p.ssn,
p.dob,
p.email,
p.phone,
p.street,
p.apt_number,
p.zip,
c.city_name as city,
p.guard_last,
p.guard_first,
p.balance,
g.gender_name as gender,
i.insurance_co as `primary insurance`,
ins.insurance_co as `secodary insurance`
FROM patient p
INNER JOIN insurance i ON p.primary_ins_id = i.id
INNER JOIN insurance ins ON p.secondary_ins_id = ins.id
INNER JOIN gender g ON p.gender_id = g.id
INNER JOIN city c ON p.city_id = c.id;

ALTER TABLE patient
ADD state varchar(2) DEFAULT 'MS' AFTER `apt_number`;

ALTER TABLE patient
MODIFY state varchar(30);

UPDATE patient
SET state = 'AL'
WHERE id = 2;

SELECT TRUNCATE(AVG(balance), 2) FROM patient;
SELECT MAX(balance) FROM patient; -- 65.10
SELECT MIN(balance) FROM patient; -- 31.61
SELECT SUM(balance) FROM patient;

-- SELECT * FROM patient WHERE balance = 65.10;
SELECT * FROM patient WHERE balance = (SELECT MAX(balance) FROM patient);

SELECT * FROM patient WHERE balance = (SELECT MIN(balance) FROM patient);

RPG Params

1. Demonstrate all basic JavaScript
a. Variables - Data types
b. Arrays, Objects
c. Conditionals
d. Loops
e. Functions
f. DOM
g. Events
2. Data models - ie options, player, monsters, events
3. Min 10 scenes
4. Go forward and backward to scenes
5. Must use increment and decrement, as well as use mathematical operators
6. Must take user events to decide direction of game - inputs, click, keypress, etc
7. Must include supporting graphics - HTML, CSS
8. Must have instructor approval

Announcement: "var changeJar =…"

Bryce Mullican
Created Nov 24, 2020Nov 24, 2020 – Deleted
This post is visible to all teachers in this class. It will be permanently deleted today.
var changeJar = ['dime','dime','dime','penny','nickel','penny','dime','quarter','dime','nickel','nickel','dime','quarter','nickel','penny','dime','nickel','dime','dime','dime','quarter','nickel','quarter','dime','nickel','penny','dime','penny','nickel','quarter','quarter','quarter','dime','nickel','dime','quarter','dime','penny','penny','nickel','penny','penny','dime','dollar']

function Drawer(change) {
this.change = change;
}

Drawer.prototype.countCoins = function countCoins(change = []) {
let dimes = 0;
let nickels = 0;
let pennies = 0;
let quarters = 0;

for (let i = 0; i < change.length; i++) {
const coin = change[i];
switch (coin) {
case 'dime':
dimes++;
break;
case 'nickel':
nickels++;
break;
case 'penny':
pennies++;
break;
case 'quarter':
quarters++;
break;
default:
break;
}
}
return {
dimes,
nickels,
pennies,
quarters
};
}

Drawer.prototype.countCash = function countCash(change = []) {
let dollars = 0;
let fives = 0;
for (let i = 0; i < change.length; i++) {
const coin = change[i];
switch (coin) {
case 'dollar':
dollars++;
break;
default:
break;
}
// dimes == 4
}
return {
dollars,
fives
}
}

Drawer.prototype.getCoins = function getCoins() {
return this.countCoins(this.change);
}

Drawer.prototype.getCash = function getCash() {
return this.countCash(this.change);
}

let drawer = new Drawer(changeJar);
console.log(drawer);
console.log(drawer.getCoins());
console.log(drawer.getCash());

}
}

getAlbumInfo() {
let button = document.getElementById('button');

event.preventDefault();
console.log('click');

let bandName = document.getElementById('bandName').value;
let album = document.getElementById('albumName').value;
let year = document.getElementById('year').value;
let label = document.getElementById('labelName').value;
// let firstInfo = document.getElementById('first');
// let lastInfo = document.getElementById('last');
// let bandInfo = document.getElementById('band');
// let albumInfo = document.getElementById('album')
// let labelInfo = document.getElementById('label');
// let yearInfo = document.getElementById('yearReleased');

this.albumInfo = {
first: firstName,

}
cards.innerHTML +=
`<div class="card">
<h2>${this.albumInfo.album}</h2>
<p>${this.albumInfo.first} ${this.albumInfo.last}</p>
<p>${this.albumInfo.band}</p>
<p>${this.albumInfo.label}</p>
<p>${this.albumInfo.year}</p>
</div>`

})
}
}

let albumData = new Album().getAlbumInfo();
